
# Development Rules for Dale Carnegie Chatbot

## General Guidelines
- Do not generate any code without explicit confirmation
- Ask for clarification if any requirement is unclear
- Use latest stable versions of all dependencies
- Follow TypeScript best practices
- Use App Router architecture for Next.js
- Implement error handling for all async operations
- Always use proper typing

## Development Order
1. Initial setup only
2. Ask before proceeding to next step
3. Confirm file structure before creating files
4. Verify dependency versions before installing

## Code Style
- Use shadcn/ui components
- Follow Next.js 14 conventions
- Use AI SDK for chat functionality
- Implement streaming responses
- Use proper TypeScript types

## Setup Process
1. Project Initialization
   - Confirm Next.js version
   - Verify dependency list
   - Check TypeScript config

2. Dependencies
   - Confirm before installing each major dependency
   - Use specific versions for stability
   - Group related dependencies

3. File Structure
   - Confirm directory structure
   - Create files one at a time
   - Verify component hierarchy

4. Components
   - Build basic structure first
   - Add functionality incrementally
   - Confirm styling approach

## Questions to Ask
1. Version confirmations
2. Directory structure verification
3. Component implementation details
4. API endpoint specifications
5. Database connection details

## Testing
- Confirm test approach before implementation
- Verify component functionality
- Test database connections